{"rendered": {"description": {"raw": "In response to issue #836 and probably useful in some other situations as our testing suite is growing with the time.\r\n\r\nI've moved all our cmake testing macros to **GazeboTestUtils.cmake**. In **GazeboUtils.cmake** they are declared empty, so we don't need to modify each CMakeLists.txt, and they are redeclared on the presence of True in  the ```ENABLE_TEST_COMPILATION``` (which for backwards compatibility is on by default) by including the GazeboTestUtils.cmake file.\r\n\r\nI've also starting a new section in the README file to document all these building options.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>In response to issue <a href=\"#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/836/missing-cmake-option-to-disable-tests\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Missing cmake option to disable tests\" class=\"ap-connect-link\"><s>#836</s></a> and probably useful in some other situations as our testing suite is growing with the time.</p>\n<p>I've moved all our cmake testing macros to <strong>GazeboTestUtils.cmake</strong>. In <strong>GazeboUtils.cmake</strong> they are declared empty, so we don't need to modify each CMakeLists.txt, and they are redeclared on the presence of True in  the <code>ENABLE_TEST_COMPILATION</code> (which for backwards compatibility is on by default) by including the GazeboTestUtils.cmake file.</p>\n<p>I've also starting a new section in the README file to document all these building options.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "title": {"raw": "Support for ENABLE_TESTS_COMPILATION cmake parameter", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Support for ENABLE_TESTS_COMPILATION cmake parameter</p>", "type": "rendered"}}, "type": "pullrequest", "description": "In response to issue #836 and probably useful in some other situations as our testing suite is growing with the time.\r\n\r\nI've moved all our cmake testing macros to **GazeboTestUtils.cmake**. In **GazeboUtils.cmake** they are declared empty, so we don't need to modify each CMakeLists.txt, and they are r